\f0\b BlocProvider:
\f1\b0 \
We usually subclass our Bloc class using BlocProvider.\
And this subclass act as a provider.\
\

\f0\b BlocListener:\

\f1\b0 It listen to changes of state of a bloc. So you can perform some side effects. Like displaying error messages, new screens etc.\
\

\f0\b BlocBuilder:\

\f1\b0 After listening the state changes to build something it is used. Like a FutureBuilder or StreamBuilder.\
\

\f0\b BlocConsumer:\

\f1\b0 Combines BlocListener and BlocBuilder.\
It Listens to changes that happen inside a Bloc, it will allow both side effect and Widget to display to the user based on those changes.\
